The paper deals with scene graph parsing, which involves understanding the relationships between objects in an image. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed contrastive loss formulations are a type of regularization technique, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on several datasets, including Visual Genome and OpenImages, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
